      "date": "2012-01-21 06:03:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified\n\nBuild Successful \n \nhttp://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/4344/ : SUCCESS",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "cfc7c030a927d436d0f3fb49d591e60ddabb394c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-01-21 22:26:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n\"Hmm, in current implementation, we will extend every small read to 1M, no matter it is random or sequence, i.e. it does not check whether it is initial read or subsequent read of a sequential access.\"  Ah, this is only true for b1_8. But on 2_x, it will only align(trim) the size to 1M, instead of extended it. So I will re-enable 101a.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
